<!DOCTYPE issue SYSTEM "lwg-issue.dtd">

<issue num="4416" status="Voting">
<title><tt>&lt;meta&gt;</tt> should include <tt>&lt;compare&gt;</tt></title>
<section><sref ref="[meta.syn]"/></section>
<submitter>Jiang An</submitter>
<date>15 Oct 2025</date>
<priority>99</priority>

<discussion>
<p>
Some inclusions from <tt>&lt;meta&gt;</tt> were removed between <paper num="P2996R7"/> and <paper num="P2996R8"/>. 
However, given `std::meta::member_offsets` has <tt>operator&lt;=&gt;</tt>, perhaps we should still include 
<tt>&lt;compare&gt;</tt> in <tt>&lt;meta&gt;</tt>. 
This is also noticed in <paper num="P3429R1"/>.
</p>

<note>2025-10-20; Reflector poll.</note>
<p>
Set status to Tentatively Ready after five votes in favour during reflector poll.
</p>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<p>
This wording is relative to <paper num="N5014"/>.
</p>

<ol>
<li><p>Modify <sref ref="[meta.syn]"/>, header <tt>&lt;meta&gt;</tt> synopsis, as indicated:</p>

<blockquote>
<pre>
<ins>#include &lt;compare&gt; // <i>see <sref ref="[compare.syn]"/></i></ins>
#include &lt;initializer_list&gt; // <i>see <sref ref="[initializer.list.syn]"/></i>

namespace std {
  [&hellip;]
}
</pre>
</blockquote>
</li>
</ol>

</resolution>

</issue>
